Clerics who take the Repose domain seek the grace of a good death, and are granted spells to combat unnecessary death.

<b>Domain Special Ability and Bonus Spells</b>
- Death Touch: The cleric can strike dead with a touch those who defy their will once per day.  With a melee touch attack, the cleric rolls d6 per caster level (double on a critical) and slays the target if their HP is less than this value.

- The cleric gains access to the following spells at the specified spell level: <i>Death Ward (3), Phantasmal Killer (4), Destruction (6), Wail of the Banshee(9)</i>.